  "prompt": "Is T-fal cookware oven safe?",
  "response": "Yes, many T-fal cookware items are oven safe, but it depends on the specific product line and the materials used in the cookware. Generally, T-fal pans with stainless steel handles can usually withstand oven temperatures up to around 500\u00b0F, while those with silicone or bakelite handles might be safe up to approximately 350\u00b0F to 400\u00b0F. It's important to check the manufacturer's guidelines for your specific T-fal product to confirm its oven safety limits, as exceeding these can damage the cookware or affect its non-stick properties. Always refer to the documentation that came with your cookware or check the official T-fal website for the most accurate information.",
